<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - LUBRICATING OIL PUMP, OIL FILTER AND COOLER - OIL COOLER - LEAKAGE
        TEST
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="2">
        <title>LEAKAGE TEST</title>
        <para>Inspect the oil cooler assembly for leaks using an "Air Pressure" test as follows:</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Construct a plate as shown in
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350811">8.11</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fasten the plate, using new oil cooler gaskets, to the cooler (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350812">8.12</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install oil filter, O-rings and all pipe plugs in headers prior to pressure checks.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">OIL SIDE PRESSURE CHECK:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Leave water side 1/4NPTF hole in plate open.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install an air pressure hose to the oil side 1/4NPT hole in plate.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Immerse the assembly in a container of clean "tap" water.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Apply 40-60 psi air pressure while immersed.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Inspect header castings, O-Ring seals and 1/4NPTF water side opening for moving or
                    growing bubbles. Replace components as required.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">WATER SIDE PRESSURE CHECK:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Leave oil side 1/4NPTF hole in plate open.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install an air pressure hose to the water side 1/4NPTF hole in plate.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Immerse the assembly in a container of "tap" water.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Apply 40-60 psi are pressure while immersed.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Inspect header castings for moving or growing bubbles. Replace components as required.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4350811" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12426a" filename="../figcg1/CG12426A.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8.11</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4350812" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg9829a" filename="../figcg9/CG9829A.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8.12</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
        </step1>
